claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: Portion of a CDC MMWR report showing a table of contents (listing sections such as Introduction, Methods, Recommendations for Use of Influenza Vaccines, Vaccine Composition and Available Vaccines, Storage and Handling, References) and editorial/production staff and citation information. does not support the claim because the image contains only the table of contents and publication credits without any data or statements about mutations in cell- or egg-based vaccine production or their impact on effectiveness. Note: The visible content is limited to front-matter and does not include any vaccine production or mutation information.
